body:
Long-standing todo which now needs immediate fixing.

Currently, enums with identical fields will alias during emission:
```mlir
hw.type_scope @fsm_enum_typedecls {
    hw.typedecl @M2_state_t : !hw.enum<A, B>
    hw.typedecl @M1_state_t : !hw.enum<A, B>
}
```
emits as
```sv
typedef enum {A, B} M2_state_t;
typedef enum {A, B} M1_state_t;
```

This commit introduces a change to ExportVerilog wherein enum prefixes are gathered before running module emission. These prefixes will be any `hw.typedecl` that declares an enum type within a `hw.type_scope` in the top-level `mlir::Module`.

Enums now work as:
```mlir
hw.type_scope @fsm_enum_typedecls {
    hw.typedecl @M2_state : !hw.enum<A, B>
    hw.typedecl @M1_state : !hw.enum<A, B>
}
```
emits as
```sv
typedef enum {M2_state_A, M2_state_B} M2_state;
typedef enum {M1_state_A, M1_state_B} M1_state;
```
